## Slice boundaries

| Layer | Slice unit | Anti-pattern |
|---|---|---|
| Step 1 UI | One `.tsx` per screen | All four screens in `step-one-form.tsx` |
| Step 2 UI | One `.tsx` per deep-dive module | Conditional blocks for gut/hormone/immune in one file |
| API | One `route.ts` per endpoint | Shared mega-handler for intake + patients |
| Pure logic | One concern per file in `lib/` | Mixed readiness + merge + triggers in one module |
| Workers | One processor per media type | Single `process-document.ts` with a giant switch |

## Failure modes (do not do these)

1. **Building `step-two-renderer.tsx` with all seven deep dives inline** because "they share the same layout" — extract shared layout to `components/ui/` if needed; modules stay separate.
2. **Adding `lib/intake/index.ts` barrel exports** that encourage importing half the domain from one entry point — import from the specific slice file.
3. **Creating files outside the tree** (e.g. `app/intake/components/SymptomForm.tsx`) without confirming the path change with the user.
4. **Putting Zod schemas inside route handlers** instead of `lib/intake/schemas/` — schemas are their own slice.
